---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Jiachuan Zhu — software engineer"
	pubDate={new Date('2026-06-18')}
>
	<p>
		I have spent most of my career building backend systems, distributed infrastructure, and
		data-intensive applications.
	</p>

	<p>
		For years, software engineering felt relatively stable. We wrote code, understood the systems
		underneath, debugged failures, and gradually developed intuition about how software behaves in
		production.
	</p>

	<p>
		Recently I started building products on my own, especially mobile applications, which pushed me
		far outside my original comfort zone and forced me to learn unfamiliar parts of the stack, from
		iOS runtime behavior to operating system boundaries.
	</p>

	<p>
		At the same time, I have been deeply experimenting with AI-assisted software development.
	</p>

	<p>
		I use systems built around OpenCode, Claude, DeepSeek, custom review agents, and structured
		design workflows to explore how large language models are changing the way software gets built.
	</p>

	<p>
		What interests me is not AI itself.
	</p>

	<p>
		What interests me is a much larger question.
	</p>

	<p>
		As AI becomes increasingly capable of generating code, what happens to software engineering as a
		discipline?
	</p>

	<p>
		I increasingly believe the future of engineering will not be defined by who writes more code.
	</p>

	<p>
		It will be defined by who better understands systems.
	</p>

	<p>
		This site is a public record of what I build, what breaks, and what I learn while navigating
		software engineering in the AI coding era.
	</p>
</Layout>
